modules.description: This module processes map-like expressions in the AST, converting key-value pairs into module expressions and constructing valid OCaml expressions for map data. It works directly with OCaml's AST types such as `expression`, `module_expr`, and `longident`, handling operations like module creation, expression transformation, and map construction. Concrete use cases include implementing custom map syntax extensions, transforming key-value sequences into structured expressions, and generating module expressions from identifiers and constructs.
